  <thing id="sogTlAvertingSwit" name="Averting Switch" compset="SoGTalent" description="Whenever a dancer would be the target of an attack or included in an instantaneous area effect that allows a Reflex save, another willing dancer that can reach them can spend an immediate action to swap spaces or the attacked dancer can spend a swift or immediate action to swap places with a willing dancer. Either way, the other dancer becomes the new target of the attack (or saving throw) and gets a +2 dodge bonus to their AC or Reflex save against the attack or effect. The bonus increases by 1 for every 6 ranks in this packageâ€™s associated skill you possess. After the attack is resolved, those dancers may choose to swap places again without using another action (if both agree).\n\nIf you have at least 5 ranks in the associated skill, the attacked dancer can also use this ability on an unwilling creature within their natural reach as an immediate action. The dancer must succeed at a reposition combat maneuver (Pathfinder Roleplaying Game: Advanced Playerâ€™s Guide) against the creature to swap places, using your ranks in this packageâ€™s associated skill in place of their base attack bonus (if they wish). As long as the dancer exceeds the creatureâ€™s CMD by 5 or more, they can choose to swap places again after the attack is resolved." uniqueness="useronce">
