  <thing id="sogTlFlowingTheat" name="Flowing Theatrics" compset="SoGTalent" description="If you possess the (act) package, whenever you would adopt the approach of an act, it does not count towards your normal limit to the amount of approaches you may adopt at one time (but you may not perform more than one act at a time). Additionally, you can adopt the approach associated with an act as a swift action instead of a move action.\n\nIf you possess the (dance) package, while you dance, each ally within the area can spend an immediate action to move 5 feet and join your dance. If the ally moves in response to an attack or an effect that allows a Reflex saving throw, it resolves before they leave their current space but the ally gets a +1 dodge bonus to AC against the attack or save. The movement provokes attacks of opportunity from anyone other than an attacker being avoided this way. For every 6 ranks you have in the (dance) packageâ€™s associated skill, the dodge bonus increases by 1.\n\nIf you possess the (lyric) package, your inspiring lyrics can be expended as a free action that can be taken even when it is not the targetâ€™s turn. Your discouraging lyrics must be expended using two swift actions or one standard action. (The lyricâ€™s expended effect only activates after the second swift action is expended.) Additionally, you may use a lyric as a swift action. If you do so, the lyric only lasts until the end of your next turn; if it is an inspiring lyric, it cannot be expended.\n\nIf you possess the (instrumental) package, you may maintain an instrumental as a swift action instead of a move action." uniqueness="useronce">
