  <thing id="sogTlIndustriousW" name="Industrious Worker" compset="SoGTalent" description="When using a skill check to earn income (such as Craft, Perform, or Profession), you earn an additional 50%; for every 5 ranks you possess in the associated skill, you earn an additional 50%. For example, if you earn 6 silver pieces from an enjoyable performance, you earn 9 silver pieces instead.\n\nIf the skill check was used to assist an establishment that provides mundane services (such as waiting tables at an inn, performing at a tavern, etc.), the quality of your performance provides the establishment more income, and in exchange they offer you routine services for free (such as free meals or a free room or cabinâ€”but not the best available).\n\nIf you are using the Downtime rules (Pathfinder Roleplaying Game: Ultimate Campaign), you gain a +2 insight bonus to any skill checks attempted to earn capital. Additionally, you treat the spending limit of Goods, Influence, and Labor within a settlement as being 25% higher." uniqueness="useronce">
